resourceIsValid

public boolean resourceIsValid(java.lang.String resourcePath)
Checks if the resource located in resourcePath is valid for this resource description. It must exist. If the resource describes a MODEL, MODEL_ELEMENT, the resource must comply with the specified metamodel URI. If the resource describes a PROJECT it must be of the nature specified.

Parameters:
resourcePath -
Returns:
true if the resource valid or false in other case
